### Phase 3: Receptionist UI

##### [NEW] [receptionist_dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/receptionist_dashboard_screen.dart)
- Simplified dashboard: Today's overview (scheduled, in-progress, completed, cancelled counts), upcoming appointments list.
- No medical data, no analytics charts.
- Quick-action buttons: "New Appointment" (call-by / walk-in).

##### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart)
- Receptionist can see all clinic appointments (filter by `clinic` not `doctor`).
- Receptionist can: create, reschedule, cancel, mark arrived.
- Receptionist **cannot**: start consultation, create treatment plans, view medical records.
- Hide "Start Consultation" / "Create Plan" buttons when role is receptionist.

##### [MODIFY] [patient_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/patients/screens/patient_list_screen.dart)
- Receptionist sees patient names, phone, appointment history.
- Receptionist **cannot** see: consultation details, treatment notes, medical records.
- When receptionist taps a patient, show limited info (contact, upcoming appointments) rather than full patient profile.

##### [MODIFY] [settings_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/settings/screens/settings_screen.dart)
- Receptionist profile: show name, username, clinic name.
- Remove clinic management, doctor management, analytics sections.
- Keep: Notifications, About, Logout.

