### Phase 6: Appointments Page UX

##### [MODIFY] [appointment_list_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/appointments/screens/appointment_list_screen.dart) (continued)

**Date scroller defaults:**
- Change `_generateDates()` to generate dates starting from **yesterday** (today - 1).
- Default scroll position: yesterday first visible, today second (so the user sees yesterday â†’ today on load).
- Add a **"Today"** pill button next to the calendar icon at the top. When tapped, it resets `_selectedDate` to today, regenerates dates, and scrolls to the default position (yesterday first, today second).

**Appointment card highlighting:**
- Accept an optional `highlightAppointmentId` parameter.
- When provided, after the list loads, auto-scroll to the matching card and animate a brief highlight (e.g., a 1-second subtle glow/border pulse).
- This is triggered when the user taps "Upcoming Today" on the dashboard.

**Dashboard â†’ Appointments linking:**

##### [MODIFY] [clinic_dashboard_screen.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/clinic_dashboard_screen.dart)
- When the "Upcoming Today" card is tapped, call `mainLayoutController.switchToTab(1)` (Appointments tab) and pass the appointment ID for highlighting.
- Same for `doctor_dashboard_screen.dart`.

##### [MODIFY] [main_layout.dart](file:///c:/App%20Development/PMS/lib/features/dashboard/screens/main_layout.dart) (continued)
- Expose a `switchToTab(int index, {String? highlightAppointmentId})` method.
- When switching to tab 1 (Appointments), pass highlight ID down to `AppointmentListScreen`.
- Use `PageView` with swipe gestures for smooth tab transitions.

